We “derive” the tax‐expense item by “adding up” the tax amounts that are recorded on the revenue (sale) lines. (In this exercise the “tax” is already computed per sale.) In other words, we scan through the “Sale…” rows and sum each row’s “tax_amount” value. (Other transactions—expenses, purchases, interest, etc.—do not have a tax amount populated.)
